-- EDP Renovaveis Says Eneop Obtains Project Finance Loan From EIB
-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 2011-12-21T07:35:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-21/edp-renovaveis-says-eneop-obtains-project-finance-loan-from-eib.html
EDP Renovaveis SA (EDPR) , the renewable-
energy unit of Portuguese utility EDP-Energias de  Portugal  SA,
said Eneop-Eolicas de Portugal SA obtained a project finance
loan of 260 million euros from the  European Investment Bank .  The financing will be used for Eneop wind energy farms in
Portugal with a capacity of 376 megawatts, EDP Renovaveis said
today in a regulatory filing.  “The closing of this transaction will allow an equity
reimbursement to Eneop’s shareholders, which have fully funded
the investment in the second group of projects through equity
contributions and shareholder loans,” EDP Renovaveis said.  The Eneop venture is ownen by partners including EDP
Renovaveis,  Enel Green Power SpA (EGPW)  and Enercon GmbH.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  